  "local_port": 58208,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I found a large range of formal and evening wear in Gold Coast?",
  "response": "If you're looking for a wide range of formal and evening wear in the Gold Coast, you're in luck! The area boasts several shopping centers and boutiques that cater to various styles and budgets. Here are some top recommendations:\n\n### 1. **Pacific Fair Shopping Centre**\nLocated in Broadbeach, Pacific Fair is one of the largest shopping destinations on the Gold Coast. It offers a diverse selection of stores where you can find formal and evening attire, including:\n\n- **David Jones**: A high-end department store featuring a curated selection of designer gowns, suits, and accessories.\n- **Myer**: Another major department store with a broad range of formal wear for both men and women.\n- **Witchery** and **Dessy Group**: For trendy and elegant evening dresses.\n- **Sportsgirl** and **Country Road**: Offering stylish options for semi-formal events.\n\n### 2. **Robina Town Centre**\nRobina Town Centre is another premier shopping hub with numerous options for formal wear:\n\n- **TS Galleries**: Known for sophisticated dresses and suits.\n- **Camilla and Marc**: Offers chic and modern evening wear.\n- **The Strand**: A variety of boutiques that specialize in formal attire.\n\n### 3. **Harbour Town Outlet Shopping Centre**\nIf you're looking for more affordable options without compromising on style:\n\n- **Outlet stores** often carry discounted formal wear from popular brands.\n- **Local boutiques**: Explore smaller shops that may offer unique and budget-friendly evening outfits.\n\n### 4. **Surfers Paradise Shopping Precinct**\nFor those near the iconic Surfers Paradise area:\n\n- **QueensPlaza**: Houses several fashion retailers with formal wear sections.\n- **The Avenue**: Features a mix of mainstream and independent stores offering evening attire.\n\n### 5. **Local Boutiques and Specialty Stores**\nExploring local boutiques can lead you to unique and personalized formal wear:\n\n- **The Boutique Collective** in Mermaid Beach: A curated selection of designer dresses and accessories.\n- **Markus John**: Known for bespoke tailoring and custom evening suits.\n\n### 6. **Brisbane Road Area**\nHome to a variety of trendy and contemporary fashion stores:\n\n- **Julius Prowse**: Offers modern and stylish evening wear.\n- **Daniel W**: For those seeking elegant and timeless gowns.\n\n### Tips for Shopping Formal and Evening Wear:\n- **Plan Ahead**: Formal events often require tailored fits, so allow ample time for alterations.\n- **Consult Store Staff**: Sales associates can provide valuable advice and help you find the perfect outfit.\n- **Check Return Policies**: Ensure you understand the store\u2019s return or exchange policies, especially if ordering online.\n\n### Additional Resources:\n- **Google Maps**: Use it to locate these shopping centers and boutiques, read reviews, and get directions.\n- **Local Fashion Events**: Keep an eye out for fashion shows or trunk shows in the Gold Coast area, which can be a great way to discover new designers and trends.\n\nBy visiting these shopping centers and exploring both large retailers and local boutiques, you should be able to find a stunning array of formal and evening wear to suit your needs on the Gold Coast. Happy shopping!",
